Files

 This file contains macros to select module names.

 This file contains the structure and APIs to register I2C handlers with PMHAL.

file  V0/pmhal_prcm.h
 This file contains enumeration declarations for different elements of PRCM like clock, module, power domain, etc. which uniquely identifies each element of PRCM.
 
file  V2/pmhal_prcm.h
 This file contains enumeration declarations for different elements of PRCM like clock, module, power domain, etc. which uniquely identifies each element of PRCM.

typedef struct pmhalPrcmPllPostDivValue pmhalPrcmPllPostDivValue_t
 Structure defining pll post divider value with post divider ID. User will use this struct to pass information to the prcm API's. The division values are 1-N (direct value written to register), so mapping to bit-field config value is not needed.
 
typedef struct pmhalPrcmDpllConfig pmhalPrcmDpllConfig_t
 This shall be used by the APIs to take configuration input from the user. This struct will not be modelled to represent a PLL.

Detailed Description

  • Contains macros to select module names
  • I2C Comm Provides APIs to register I2C handlers with PMHAL.
  • The MPU LPRM Manager is the software HAL which provides register abstraction for accessing the local PRCM of the MPU subsystem.
  • The PRM INT provides PRM Interrupt interface declarations.

Consists of List of Domains and enum for the same, They can be divided as

  • Power Domains
  • Clock Domains
  • Voltage Domains
  • Reset Domains

Also provides API Infrastructure for the following:

enum pmhalPrcmCdClkTrnModes

Enum defining clock domain control values. These values can be used to control the clock domain while initializing the system, entering sleep state and waking up from sleep state.

Enumerator
PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_NO_SLEEP 

No sleep in the clock domain

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_SW_SLEEP 

Start a software forced sleep transition on the clock domain.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_SW_WAKEUP 

Start a software forced wake-up transition on the clock domain.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_HW_AUTO 

If there is no activity in the clock domain HW automatically puts it into sleep mode. On detecting any activity it wakes up.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_NO_SLEEP 

No sleep in the clock domain

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_SW_SLEEP 

Start a software forced sleep transition on the clock domain.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_SW_WAKEUP 

Start a software forced wake-up transition on the clock domain.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_HW_AUTO 

If there is no activity in the clock domain HW automatically puts it into sleep mode. On detecting any activity it wakes up.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

Start a software forced sleep transition on the clock domain.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_SW_WAKEUP 

Start a software forced wake-up transition on the clock domain.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_HW_AUTO 

If there is no activity in the clock domain HW automatically puts it into sleep mode. On detecting any activity it wakes up.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_CD_CLKTRNMODES_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

enum pmhalPrcmDpllBypassClkSel

Enum defining bypass input clock selection for the PLL. The bypass clock can either be CLKINP (Master Osc) or CLKINPULOW (above enum value).

Enumerator
PMHAL_PRCM_DPLL_BYP_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_DPLL_BYP_CLKINP 

Select CLKINP (Master Oscillator) as the bypass mode clock.

PMHAL_PRCM_DPLL_BYP_CLKINPULOW 

Select CLKINPULOW as the bypass mode clock. Refer prcmDpllClkInputLowSel_t for possible inputs for CLKINPULOW.

PMHAL_PRCM_DPLL_BYP_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_DPLL_BYP_COUNT 

Count value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

Select CLKINP (Master Oscillator) as the bypass mode clock.

PMHAL_PRCM_DPLL_BYP_CLKINPULOW 

Select CLKINPULOW as the bypass mode clock. Refer prcmDpllClkInputLowSel_t for possible inputs for CLKINPULOW.

enum pmhalPrcmModuleMStbyState

Enum defining standby states of the module (Master only). These values can be used to check the state of the module after configuring the module mode property.

Enumerator
PMHAL_PRCM_CLKCTRL_STBYST_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MSTANDBYSTATE_FUNCTIONAL 

When master module wants to initiate a transaction on the device interconnect and it requests specific (functional and interface) clocks for that purpose. The PRCM module ensures that the required clocks are active and the module is said to be functional after this transition completes.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MSTANDBYSTATE_STANDBY 

When the master module no longer requires the clocks, it informs the PRCM module, which can then gate the clocks to the module.

PMHAL_PRCM_CLKCTRL_STBYST_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_CLKCTRL_STBYST_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MSTANDBYSTATE_FUNCTIONAL

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MSTANDBYSTATE_STANDBY 

When the master module no longer requires the clocks, it informs the PRCM module, which can then gate the clocks to the module.

PMHAL_PRCM_CLKCTRL_STBYST_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

enum pmhalPrcmModuleSIdleState

Enum defining idle states of the module. These values can be used to check the state of the module after configuring the module mode property.

Enumerator
PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_IDLEST_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_FUNCTIONAL 

Module is functional and can be accessed

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_INTRANSITION 

Module is performing transition: wakeup, or sleep,or sleep abortion

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_INTERFACE_IDLE 

Module is in Idle mode (only interface part). It is functional if it uses separate functional clock

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_DISABLED 

Module is in Idle mode (both functional and Interface)

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_IDLEST_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_DETERMINED_BY_CLK_STATE 

Used when there is no CLKCTRL register. The module state is determined by the clock state. Used in PMLIBSysConfig.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_IDLEST_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_FUNCTIONAL 

Module is functional and can be accessed

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_INTRANSITION 

Module is performing transition: wakeup, or sleep,or sleep abortion

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_INTERFACE_IDLE 

Module is in Idle mode (only interface part). It is functional if it uses separate functional clock

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_DISABLED 

Module is in Idle mode (both functional and Interface)

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_IDLEST_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_SIDLESTATE_DETERMINED_BY_CLK_STATE 

Used when there is no CLKCTRL register. The module state is determined by the clock state. Used in PMLIBSysConfig.

Used when there is no CLKCTRL register. The module state is determined by the clock state. Used in PMLIBSysConfig.

enum pmhalPrcmModuleSModuleMode

Enum defining different modes of a module.

Enumerator
PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MODE_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MODE_DISABLED 

Disabled: Any access to module registers will result in error

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MODE_AUTO 

Auto: Clocks will be gated automatically when there is no activity and enabled when there is an activity.

PMHAL_PRCM_MODULE_MODE_ENABLED 

Enabled: Functional and interface clocks are available and access to module registers are permitted.

enum pmhalPrcmPdState

Enum defining power domain status values. These values can be used to control the clock domain while initializing the system, entering sleep state and waking up from sleep state.

Enumerator
PMHAL_PRCM_PD_STATUS_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_PD_STATE_OFF 

Power to the domain is off.

PMHAL_PRCM_PD_STATE_RETENTION 

Power to the domain is in retention mode and it will not be functional but the memory will be retained.

PMHAL_PRCM_PD_STATE_ON_INACTIVE 

Power to the domain is ON INACTIVE.

PMHAL_PRCM_PD_STATE_ON_ACTIVE 

Power to the domain is ON.

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

enum pmhalPrcmPmicRegulatorId

The Abstract PMIC Voltage Regulator IDs used by the PMIC Interface. These abstract regulator IDs represent the regulators connected to the voltage rail of the respective voltage domains. The mapping of these abstract regulator IDs to the actual PMIC regulators are done in the respective HW PMIC module.

enum pmhalPrcmRootClkType

Enum defining different types of root clock.

Enumerator
PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_FIXED 

Frequency of the root clock is fixed in the SoC.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_STATIC_CONFIG 

Frequency of the root clock is not fixed in the SoC, but fixed during board design or system initialization.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_COUNT 

Count value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_MIN 

Min value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_FIXED 

Frequency of the root clock is fixed in the SoC.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_STATIC_CONFIG

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_MAX 

Max value of the enum. Can be used for validation.

PMHAL_PRCM_ROOT_CLK_FREQ_COUNT

pmErrCode_t PMHALI2CCommRegister ( const pmhalI2cCommOperations_t *  i2cfunc)

API to register the I2C initialization, read and write functions with the PMIC and INA226 communication HAL.

Parameters
i2cfuncThe structure containing function pointers to the I2C initialization, read and write functions. Refer pmhalI2cCommOperations_t for structure details
Returns
status PM_SUCCESS - If the I2C functions are registered correctly. PM_FAIL - If the I2C functions are not registered correctly.
int32_t PMHALMpuLprmClearForceOff ( uint32_t  cpuId)

Function to Clear the force off bit for CPU1 to not go to force off.

Parameters
cpuIdID of the CPU for whom force off should be set. 1 - for CPU1
Returns
status PM_SUCCESS If the CPU is forced off. PM_BADARGS If the cpuId provided is not 1.

Function to clear the HG_EN bit for disallowing MPU Mercury retention.

Returns
None.

pmhalPrcmPdState_t *  lastPowerState 
)

Function to read the last power state in which the MPU core was in.

Parameters
cpuIdID of the CPU whose power mode one wants to set. 0 - for CPU0 and 1 - for CPU1
lastPowerStateThis field is populated with the last power state. Refer enum pmhalPrcmPdState_t for details.
Returns
status PM_SUCCESS If the last power state is read correctly PM_BADARGS If the cpuId provided is neither 0 nor 1 or the pointer lastPowerState is NULL.

int32_t PMHALMpuLprmSetHgRampParams ( const pmhalMpuLprmHgRampParams_t *  hgRampParam)

Function to set the Mercury Retention ramp parameters. This is to be used only If the HG_EN bit is set.

Parameters
hgRampParamStructure which holds the parameters to be set for correct mercury retention ramp. If fast ramp is used then no need to fill the hgSlowRampTime field.
Returns
status PM_SUCCESS If the ramp parameters are set correctly. PM_BADARGS If the slow ramp is enabled and the ramp time provided is 0.

Returns

pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t  intId 
)

Parameters

intIdUnique ID of the interrupt line one wants to disable. Refer pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t for details.
Returns

int32_t PMHALPrmIntEnableAllInts ( pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t  cpuId)

This function allows enabling all the interrupts of the PRM for a given CPU using the Interrupt Enable register.

Parameters
cpuIdUnique ID of the CPU for which all interrupts should be enabled. Refer pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t for details.
Returns
status Status of the API is returned. PM_SUCCESS If the interrupts are enabled correctly. PM_BADARGS If the CPU ID is incorrect.
int32_t PMHALPrmIntEnableInterrupt ( pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t  cpuId,
pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t  intId 
)

This function allows enabling a single interrupt line from the PRM for a given CPU. Register abstraction is provided by this API.

Parameters
cpuIdUnique ID of the CPU for which the interrupt should be enabled. Refer pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t for details.
intIdUnique ID of the interrupt line one wants to enable. Refer pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t for details.
Returns
status Status of the API is returned. PM_SUCCESS If the interrupt is enabled correctly. PM_BADARGS If the CPU ID, INT ID is incorrect.
int32_t PMHALPrmIntGetEnabledInts ( pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t  cpuId,
uint64_t *  interrupts 
)

This function allows reading all the SW enabled interrupts for a given CPU from the Interrupt Enable register.

Parameters
cpuIdUnique ID of the CPU for which the interrupt should be read. Refer pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t for details.
interruptsThe interrupts which are enabled are returned in this variable. This parameter is 64 bits as the MPU has 2 registers in which it stores the interrupts that are enabled.
Returns
status Status of the API is returned. PM_SUCCESS If the interrupts are read correctly. PM_BADARGS If the CPU ID is incorrect or interrupts is NULL.
int32_t PMHALPrmIntGetStatus ( pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t  cpuId,
pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t  intId,
uint32_t *  isSet 
)

This function allows getting the status of an interrupt of the PRM for a given CPU using the Interrupt Status register.

Parameters
cpuIdUnique ID of the CPU for which all interrupts should be enabled. Refer pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t for details.
intIdUnique ID of the interrupt line one wants to get the status of. Refer pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t for details.
isSetThis variable returns the status of the interrupt 1 - Interrupt is pending. 0 - Interrupt is not pending.
Returns
status Status of the API is returned. PM_SUCCESS If the interrupt status is got correctly. PM_BADARGS If the CPU ID, INT ID is incorrect or isSet is NULL.
int32_t PMHALPrmIntWaitforInt ( pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t  cpuId,
pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t  intId,
uint32_t  timeout 
)

This function allows waiting for a given interrupt to occur. This is used for polling for an interrupt.

Parameters
cpuIdUnique ID of the CPU for which to wait. Refer pmhalPrcmSocCpuId_t for details.
intIdUnique ID of the interrupt line one wants to wait for. Refer pmhalPrcmPrmIntId_t for details.
timeoutIndicates the number of iterations to wait for the interrupt to get set in the status. Valid values for time out can be: (1) Non Zero value for which the code would wait. (2) PM_TIMEOUT_INFINITE for which the code would wait till the interrupt is received.
Returns
status Status of the API is returned. PM_SUCCESS If the interrupt is received correctly. PM_BADARGS If the CPU ID, INT ID is incorrect. PM_FAIL If the interrupt is not received in the given time out or if time out provided is 0 or PM_TIMEOUT_NOWAIT
